   ROSENFELD-COLUMN (Albany, N.Y.) _ The century now in its
concluding years certainly was savage and bloody minded, a time
when tyrants or fools reigned too long, and men and women and the
nations in which they lived suffered grievously. It is good to be
reminded, then, that all was not lost during these 100 years. By
