</P>
<P>
   DOLLAR (Undated) _ The dollar trades at its highest level
against the yen in seven years, receiving another boost when a
Japanese official dashes hopes that the major industrialized
nations will agree to support the yen. The American currency is
trading as high as 140.8 yen. In another development, the Bank for
International Settlements says in its annual report that the dollar
is overvalued by 21 percent against the mark and almost 33 percent
against the yen. By Jonathan Fuerbinger.
</P>
<P>
   AOL-MIRABILIS (Undated) _ America Online buys an Internet chat
and messaging company, Mirabilis, for $287 million in cash plus
contingent payments of as much as $120 million. The Israeli company
has never been profitable. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
<P>
   BELLATLANTIC-NETWORK (Undated) _ Bell Atlantic becomes the
latest telecom giant to plan a data network. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   NEW-REFINERY (Undated) _ Teams of workers are putting the
finishing touches on a $660 million refurbishing of a huge refinery
that had been rusting away until four years ago. The refinery, just
northeast of New Orleans, will represent the largest single
addition of refining capacity since the late 1970's. It illustrates
the sweeping changes in the industry, which in recent years has
gone from having too much capacity to having to rush in imports
from Europe and Latin America because of booming demand for
gasoline. By Agis Salpukas.
</P>
