that had been rusting away until four years ago. The refinery, just
northeast of New Orleans, will represent the largest single
addition of refining capacity since the late 1970s. It illustrates
the sweeping changes in the industry, which in recent years has
gone from having too much capacity to having to rush in imports
from Europe and Latin America because of booming demand for
gasoline. By Agis Salpukas.
