<HEADLINE>
GAY FELLOWSHIP: NEW FACILITIES TO ACCOMMODATE MEETINGS IN HOUSTON 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By CLIFFORD PUGH 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ For years, Houston has been about the only major U.S.
city without a community center where gays and lesbians can gather
to discuss issues or hold a potluck dinner in a safe and homey
environment.
</P>
<P>
   But that's recently changed with the opening of two new
facilities.
</P>
<P>
   The Houston Lesbian and Gay Community Center opened recently in
an artsy section of the city known as the Montrose area. The
