<TEXT>
<P>
   GOLF SPECIAL SECTION
</P>
<P>
   Copy from The Atlanta Journal-Constitution special tab section
on golf is moving now. The section looks at the people, the playing
and the products of golf. Photos are available, and two sets of
facing tab pages are being posted on fashion and equipment. For
more information, please call CoxNet news manager Paul Foutch at
404-526-5429.
</P>
<P>
   THE PEOPLE
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-FAMILY _ A personal look at the game of golf and what it's
meant to staff writer Michelle Hiskey, niece of pro player Babe
Hiskey, whose family has been involved in the game for years. Some
of her fondest family memories involve golf; family members played
golf on the day of her grandfather's funeral at a course he
designed; she's also a former college player at Duke University.
Now, when she looks at her infant daughter, she wonders if she,
too, will take up this bigger-than-life game. (Hiskey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-WOMEN _ Women and golf have not traditionally been a match.
But more and more women are taking up the game these days, using
golf for leverage in the business world or as a way to spend more
time with their husbands. What obstacles (prejudices, club
restrictions, etc.) do female newcomers to the game face and how
can they overcome them? (Hiskey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-BLACKS _ A look at the African-American golf scene. With
its growing black middle class, great weather and large number of
courses, Atlanta, for example, has a huge contingent of
African-Americans taking up the sport. (Wilkinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-KIDS _ What parents of Tiger Woods wanne-bes should know
about getting youngsters started in golf, from equipment advice to
instruction. (Rosen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-MARSHAL _ They make sure there aren't any fights on the
first tee and everyone goes off in order. If you play slow, they
tell you to speed it up. They have everything but a badge. They are
the few, the proud, the golf course marshals. (Hiskey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   THE PLAYING
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-FITNESS _ What exercises can golfers do specifically aimed
at improving their golf game? We talk to fitness and golf expert
Kelly Blackburn, who works with several professional players, and
give advice about a ``Golfer's Workout.'' (Kim, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-FITNESS-QNA _ Answering fitness questions about golf.
(Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-SCHOOLS _ You can never stop learning about golf, so why
not combine a trip with a little instruction? A look at golf camps
in the Southeast. (Thrasher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-PRACTICE _ Believe it or not, there is a right way to
practice your golf game. Everyone seems to want to grab their
driver first when they hit the practice range, but that may not be
the best idea. We talk to experts for advice. (Rosen, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-HUMMER _ AJC columnist Steve Hummer visits the swing
doctor, learning his tee shot is in critical shape, but that it can
be saved. (Hummer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   THE PRODUCTS
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-FASHION _ Two-page spread on latest trends in golf duds.
(Walton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) NO STORY. PHOTOS AND LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-EQUIPMENT _ New golf equipment for 1998. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) NO STORY. WITH PHOTOS AND LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF-INTERNET _ The best golf sites for participants. (Davidson,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
