<HEADLINE>
WHITE-HOT  
 (JT) 
</HEADLINE>
   By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Even die-hard fashion aficionados who live in black
most of the year add a touch of white in the summer. Here are some
suggestions.
</P>
<P>
   Saks Fifth Avenue is offering brimmed hats in white canvas
($175) by Sonia Rykiel, narrow white belts with silver buckles
($145) by Gucci and white cotton sundresses ($140) by ABS Studio
that have ribbon and lace trimming.
</P>
<P>
   Nordstrom has Ralph Lauren polo shirts ($39) in white and a
linen-and-silk pants suit (jacket, $124; pants, $88) by Classiques
Entier.
</P>
<P>
   Barneys New York has a long white skirt ($115) by Martin
Margiela, a short white embroidered skirt ($170) by Jill Stuart, a
sleeveless cotton dress ($120) by Ann Demeulemeester and, in the
Co-op, white shorts ($75) and slim pants ($95).
</P>
<P>
   Bergdorf Goodman has a white pique shift ($495) in its
private-label collection, a camisole ($445) and pants ($440) by
Richard Tyler and a long linen-blend dress ($790) by H. Lam.
</P>
