<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-08 19:03 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9703 &Cx1f; tab-z
w e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-X-FILES-QUIZ-STARBEAT     06-08 1451
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-X-FILES-QUIZ-STARBEAT-ART-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE X-FILES: THE QUIZ 
</HEADLINE>
  (This ``separate buy'' article is from this week's StarBeat
entertainment package.) 
 (To publish this article, it must be purchased _ the rate is not
prohibitive _ from New York Times Syndicate sales representative
CONNIE WHITE in Kansas City at 1-800-444-0267 or 816-822-8448, or
by fax at 816-822-1444.) 
 (She also has information on how to subscribe to StarBeat, a weekly
package of five intriguing features with color art.) 
 Includes a color slide of David Duchovny and Gillian Anderson in a
scene from ``The X-Files.'' 
 By TOM FRANGICETTO  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
 &HT;    Its code name is ``Blackwood,'' it will be landing in theaters
everywhere on June 19 and the anticipation of its arrival has
aroused one of television's most loyal cults.
 &HT;    It is the ``X-Files'' movie, and it is expected to finally
reveal many of the elusive secrets that agents Fox Mulder and Dana
Scully have been pursuing for five years.
 &HT;    Whether you're a rabid X-phile or merely on the cusp of being a
``believer,'' here is a 16-question inquiry to probe your knowledge
of ... the truth. 
 -0- 
 &HT;    1. In the pilot episode, Dr. Dana Scully gives what reason for
choosing to work for the FBI rather than practice medicine?
 &HT;    a. It was an act of rebellion against her parents.
 &HT;    b. She's a type-A personality who thrives on intrigue.
 &HT;    c. She saw it as a place where she could distinguish herself.
 &HT;    d. She wanted to contribute to humanity.
 &HT;    2. Fox Mulder is a trained psychologist. What university did he
attend, and on what subject did he write a monograph?
 &HT;    a. Oxford, and serial killers and the occult
 &HT;    b. Harvard, and serial killers and ESP
 &HT;    c. Yale, and serial killers and the paradox of paranormal
experience
 &HT;    d. Princeton, and serial killers and the nature/nurture debate.
 &HT;    3. What was Mulder's nickname at the FBI Academy?
 &HT;    a. ``Old Eerie''
 &HT;    b. ``The Weirdo''
 &HT;    c. ``Flaky''
 &HT;    d. ``Spooky.''
 &HT;    4. Scully is assigned to assist Mulder with the X-Files and to
write ``field reports on the validity of the work.''
 &HT;    Scully interprets this to mean she is to ...
 &HT;    a. discredit Mulder.
 &HT;    b. verify the authenticity of Mulder's claims.
 &HT;    c. debunk the X-Files project.
 &HT;    d. spy on Mulder.
 &HT;    5. In the second episode, Mulder is contacted by ``Deep
Throat,'' a mysterious informant. When Mulder asks, ``They're here,
aren't they?'' what does he say?
 &HT;    a. ``Mr. Mulder, you'll need to dig a little deeper to learn the
answer to that question.''
 &HT;    b. ``Mr. Mulder, does the word `paranoid' mean anything to
you?''
 &HT;    c. ``Mr. Mulder, they've been here for a long, long time.''
 &HT;    d. ``Mr. Mulder, it's time for you to finally open your eyes and
face the truth.''
 &HT;    6. Mulder's quest for ``the truth'' is mainly motivated by his
search for his sister, who may have been abducted by aliens. What
was his sister's name and how old was she when she vanished?
 &HT;    a. Sabrina, age 5
 &HT;    b. Amanda, age 6
 &HT;    c. Cassandra, age 7
 &HT;    d. Samantha, age 8.
 &HT;    7. In the first-season finale, Deep Throat is murdered. What are
his dying words to Scully?
 &HT;    a. ``Tell Mulder I'm sorry.''
 &HT;    b. ``Trust no one.''
 &HT;    c. ``Tell Mulder the truth is still out there.''
 &HT;    d. ``Save yourself while you can.''
 &HT;    8. How does Mulder attend Deep Throat's funeral?
 &HT;    a. disguised as Mulder's alias, George B. Hale
 &HT;    b. using eight-power binoculars from 1,000 feet away
 &HT;    c. as a pallbearer
 &HT;    d. as the driver of the hearse.
 &HT;    9. The first season ended with the X-Files being closed down. In
the opening episode of the second season, Mulder has a secret
rendezvous with another person.
 &HT;    Who is it, and where do they meet?
 &HT;    a. Scully, in the basement of the Watergate Hotel and Office
Complex
 &HT;    b. A man known only as ``Mr. X,'' in the Watergate Hotel and
Office Complex
 &HT;    c. An unidentified man who later becomes Assistant Director
Skinner, in Arlington Cemetery
 &HT;    d. The Cigarette-Smoking Man, at the Lincoln Memorial.
 &HT;    10. The ubiquitous, ever-enigmatic Cigarette-Smoking Man seems
to be involved in many sinister schemes and events.
 &HT;    Which of the following statements did he not make to Mulder?
 &HT;    a. ``I've watched presidents die.''
 &HT;    b. ``When you look at me, Mr. Mulder, imagine that you are
looking at the face of God.''
 &HT;    c. ``I like you.''
 &HT;    d. ``If people were to know of the things I know, it would all
fall apart.''
 &HT;    11. Scully is kidnapped by a deranged ``abductee,'' is possibly
abducted herself and eventually appears at a Washington hospital in
a coma.
 &HT;    Who kidnapped her?
 &HT;    a. Luther Lee Boggs
 &HT;    b. Duane Barry
 &HT;    c. Eddie Van Blundht
 &HT;    d. Eugene Victor Tooms.
 &HT;    Bonus: Name the actor who played the kidnapper and the role that
he is most noted for.
 &HT;    12. The last episode of the third season and the first of the
fourth further a theme many expect to be developed in the upcoming
``X-Files'' movie _ the alien colonization of the earth.
 &HT;    What is the name of the healer alien who tells Mulder about this
plot?
 &HT;    a. Jeremiah Smith
 &HT;    b. Jose Chung
 &HT;    c. Alonzo Bilac
 &HT;    d. Brian Thompson.
 &HT;    13. ``Those are the most paranoid people I have ever met,''
Scully declares.
 &HT;    Who's she talking about?
 &HT;    a. the Lone Gunmen
 &HT;    b. CIA agents
 &HT;    c. the police department in Alexandria, Va.
 &HT;    d. agents with the FBI Sci-Crime Lab.
 &HT;    14. Much of the mythology of ``The X-Files'' is turned upside
down by a character who tells Mulder about an elaborate hoax to
mislead him.
 &HT;    Who is that character?
 &HT;    a. Alex Krycek
 &HT;    b. Ashley Montagu
 &HT;    c. Scott Ostelhoff
 &HT;    d. Michael Kritschgau.
 &HT;    Bonus: Which of these men killed Mulder's father?
 &HT;    15. ``We predict the future, and the best way to predict the
future is to invent it.''
 &HT;    Who offers Scully this confident assertion?
 &HT;    a. The Cigarette-Smoking Man
 &HT;    b. The Well-Manicured Man
 &HT;    c. Deep Throat
 &HT;    d. ``Mr. X.''
 &HT;    16. What is the slogan on the most prominent poster in Mulder's
office?
 &HT;    a. ``I WANT TO BELIEVE''
 &HT;    b ``THE TRUTH IS OUT THERE''
 &HT;    c. ``HANG IN THERE, BABY''
 &HT;    d. ``KEEP WATCHING THE SKIES.''
 &HT;    Bonus: Where did Mulder get the poster?
 ANSWERS  
 &HT;    1. c _ Scully hopes to get ahead, but instead regularly risks
getting killed.
 &HT;    2. a _ Mulder is an Oxford man, and his monograph on serial
killers and the occult turns out to have been very handy for his
future career.
 &HT;    3. d _ Fox ``Spooky'' Mulder was considered immensely talented,
but his offbeat interests drew skepticism even before he met
Scully.
 &HT;    4. c _ Scully's efforts at debunking have, however, grown
progressively more strained.
 &HT;    5. c _ Of course, Deep Throat can't necessarily be trusted,
either.
 &HT;    6. d _ Fox and Samantha were playing Stratego when she was
taken.
 &HT;    7. b _ ``Trust no one,'' a good motto for the series in general.
 &HT;    8. b _ Mulder watches the funeral through binoculars.
 &HT;    9. a _ The two meet at the Watergate, which has its own history
of hidden secrets.
 &HT;    10. b _ Fortunately, since the CSM is hardly godlike in
appearance.
 &HT;    11. b _ Barry was played by Steve Railsback, who played another
deranged character, Charles Manson, in the 1976 film, ``Helter
Skelter.''
 &HT;    12. a _ Jeremiah Smith is definitely more than he seems.
 &HT;    13. a _ The Gunmen actually manage to be more paranoid than
Mulder himself, if a bit less coherent.
 &HT;    14. d _ Kritschgau reveals the plot, but it's Krycek who killed
Mulder's father.
 &HT;    15. b _ The Well-Manicured Man claims to control the future.
Even if they did, the other three would be unlikely to be so
forthcoming.
 &HT;    16. a _ Mulder found the ``I WANT TO BELIEVE'' poster at a head
shop on M Street.
 SCORING  
 &HT;    Give yourself one point for each correct answer, plus one point
for any correct bonus answers. See below for scoring.
 &HT;    16+ _ X-quisite
 &HT;    13 to 14 _ X-cellent
 &HT;    9 to 12 _ X-ceptional
 &HT;    5 to 8 _ unX-traordinary
 &HT;    1 to 4 _ X-asperating
 &HT;    0 _ inX-cusable.
 c.1998 Tom Frangicetto  
