<SLUG> BC-ENGINEERS-MONEY09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Engineering graduates are shown the money
 &HT;    By Gene Tharpe
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Wonder why those new college graduates with
engineering degrees are smiling? Because they are being offered big
bucks by employers.
</P>
<P>
   Jobtrak Corp., which operates an online job-listing site that
links employers, universities and students, said a May survey of
selected schools nationwide found that engineering graduates were
being offered an average starting salary of $58,513, the highest of
24 careers measured by the survey.
</P>
<P>
   The Los Angeles-based firm, online at www.jobtrak.com, said all
college graduates are reaping the benefits of the expanding
economy, with 21 percent more job openings posted last month than a
year ago. The average starting salary for all 24 careers was
$46,757.
</P>
<P>
   Jobtrak, which began operations in 1987, makes monthly surveys
of job postings and hiring trends to determine which college
graduates are most in demand by employers. The May survey is the
first to measure starting salaries.
</P>
<P>
   Compared to May last year, the demand for education graduates
was up 147 percent, the most of any career, but the average
starting salary of $33,038 was well below the average.
</P>
<P>
   The lowest-paid career was ``parks and recreation'' graduates.
They may enjoy the outdoors but, with an average starting salary of
$17,000, they won't have much more to enjoy.
</P>
<P>
   Jobtrak's network includes more than 750 universities or other
institutions of higher learning, but it did not say how many
schools were involved in the survey.
</P>
<P>
   CHART: HOTTEST FIELDS
</P>
<P>
   Job category Starting salary
</P>
<P>
   Sales and marketing $34,601
</P>
<P>
   Computers &AMP; information sciences $41,480
</P>
<P>
   Business and management $36,059
</P>
<P>
   Accounting and finance $36,205
</P>
<P>
   Engineering $58,513
</P>
<P>
   Clerical and secretarial $29,992
</P>
<P>
   Education $33,038
</P>
<P>
   Public affairs and social services $26,133
</P>
<P>
   Communications/media $27,498
</P>
<P>
   Customer service $26,788
</P>
<P>
   Based on percentage of jobs posted by job category. Source:
Jobtrak
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
