<HEADLINE>
SCIENTOLOGY AT THE CORE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVID BLOOM  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ To some extent, Sky Dayton's decision to bring in
Garry Betty as his company's CEO has provided useful insulation
from complaints about Dayton's own Scientology beliefs.
</P>
<P>
   Dayton said he used Scientology management tenets to structure
the company, but his managers ``are a very diverse group'' who
bring a variety of management skills to the company.
</P>
<P>
   But Dayton, who took management classes through Scientology's
Hubbard College of Management, also says the approaches he learned
there work well with the decentralized, nonhierarchical nature of
the Internet and successful companies in that business.
</P>
<P>
   ``The tenets are pretty straightforward, and really were ahead
of their time,'' Dayton said. ``It pushes responsibility down to
the people who do the job. It's been very helpful for me and
allowed me to stay focused on my job.''
</P>
</TEXT>
