<HEADLINE>
COMPANY NEWS 
(HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
  c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Revlon Inc., New York, thea maker of beauty products, said it
would dispose of its 85 percent stake in Cosmetic Center Inc.,
Savage, Md., a retailer, and take a charge of $15 million in the
second quarter related to the sale.
</P>
<P>
   Aydin Corp., Horsham, Pa., a maker of electronic communications
systems, plans to sell three divisions to help pay a $17.2-million
arbitration award in a contract dispute to Loral Defense Systems,
now owned by the Lockheed Martin Corp., Bethesda, Md.
</P>
<P>
   Dana Corp., Toledo, Ohio, the supplier of equipment parts to
auto makers, sold its hydraulic cylinder unit to Hyco International
Inc., Atlanta, a unit of Center Partners Management LLC, New York,
for an undisclosed price.
</P>
