<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Tuesday, June 9 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   WELLS-FUTURE (Los Angeles) _ The banking supermarket is coming,
and not over by the bakery section of your grocery store, either.
Banks are scrambling to broaden the range of financial products
they offer, led by such fast-moving players as Norwest Corp., which
agreed Monday to merge with Wells Fargo in a $31 billion deal. By
Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``n'' California, ``a'' national and
``f'' financial news files.)
</P>
<P>
   CAREGIVER-SURVIVORS (Los Angeles) _ A mother's work may never
end, but she probably has longer to do it because primary
caregivers tend to outlive their mates, according to a Caltech
study released Monday. By Alex Roth. (Will move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
