A9975 &Cx1f; taf-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NYT-CORRECTIONS &LR;      06-08 0439
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NYT-CORRECTIONS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, JUNE 9
</HEADLINE>
  Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CORRUPT-SHERIFF-NYT (moved on Sunday, May 31)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday May 31,
about a small-town Alabama publishing couple who exposed corruption
by a county sheriff misstated the sentence received by the sheriff,
Roger Davis of Marengo County, for extortion. It was 27 months in
prison, not 27 years, and is to be served concurrently with another
27-month sentence, for soliciting a bribe and failure to pay state
income taxes.
</P>
<P>
   The article also misstated the age of the editor and publisher,
Goodloe Sutton of the weekly Democrat-Reporter in Linden. He is 59,
not in his late 40's.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, the article referred imprecisely to the timing of a
Democrat-Reporter article about Sheriff Davis's use of county money
for an all-terrain vehicle for his daughter. That article was
published after the sheriff had repaid the money, not before.
</P>
<P>
   The article also misstated the process by which the sheriff took
money from the county mental health center. He had the center write
a check to him for each mental patient who was transported by
sheriff's deputies; he was not cashing checks that had been
intended for the center.
</P>
<P>
   The article also misstated the circulation of The
Democrat-Reporter. It is 7,125, not 6,000.
</P>
<P>
   BC-INTERNET-U.S.-NYT (moved on Friday, June 5)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, June 5,
about the management of Internet addresses misstated the year that
the suffix ``.com'' was introduced for commercial enterprises. It
was 1985, not 1990.
</P>
<P>
   BC-PLUNDERED-ART-NYT (moved on Thursday, June 4)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, June 4,
about a pledge by American museums to search their collections for
artworks taken illegally from owners in the Nazi era misstated the
name of the group that announced the plan. It is the Association of
Art Museum Directors, not the Association of American Art Museum
Directors.
</P>
<P>
   BC-KURT-FILM-REVIEW-NYT (moved on Thursday, June 4)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, June 4,
contained a listing of credits with a film review of ``Kurt and
Courtney'' included an incorrect given name, provided by the
production company, for the producer. She is Michele D'Acosta, not
Michael.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
