<SLUG> BC-NYC-BUSINESS-BRIEF-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK'S BATTERY PARK CITY PLANS NEW BUILDING  
 (HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
   By TERRY PRISTIN   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ More than 60 developers have been invited to submit
proposals for a residential building at the northern end of Battery
Park City and are being encouraged to design large apartments for
families, officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The 300,000-square-foot apartment building is to be located
between Warren Street and Park Place West and alongside River
Terrace. The site will probably accommodate 250 to 300 apartments,
said Enid Feist, the vice president for policy and operations of
the Battery Park City Authority, the public benefit corporation
that is overseeing the development of the neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
   The site to be developed is near Stuyvesant High School and a
new school that is opening in the fall. Battery Park City residents
are being given preference for the new school, Public
School/Intermediate School 89.
</P>
<P>
   In its May 29 mailing to developers, the authority notified them
that it ``has a preference for more two- and three-bedroom units
and is seeking developments and apartments whose designs contribute
to better housing for families.''
</P>
<P>
   The proposed designs are due by July 24. They will be considered
by a five-member committee, which will make its recommendation to
the authority, Ms. Feist said. She said no decision is expected
before the end of the year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-08-98 2259EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
